==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incompliance
<hw>In`com*pli"ance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The quality or state of being incompliant; unyielding temper;
obstinacy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Self-conceit produces peevishness and <qex>incompliance</qex> of
humor in things lawful and indifferent.</q>
<rj><qau>Tillotson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Refusal or failure to comply.</def>
<rj><au>Strype.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incompliant</ent>⟦br⟧
